03:20:20.583 --> 03:20:24.941
Pr-ussians, Prussians is a good idea.

03:20:27.610 --> 03:20:30.400
Thank you, thank you very much,
beautiful idea.

03:20:30.638 --> 03:20:34.553
I’ll see this. This should be…
is a good idea.

03:20:37.426 --> 03:20:42.006
Now, I hope – still? Wah wah wah.

03:20:42.667 --> 03:20:45.770
Yogi 1: Next ashram? Amsterdam ashram?
Yogi 2: Vermeer.

03:20:45.971 --> 03:20:50.609
Yogi: No, painting from Vermeer.
Shri Mataji: Painting?

03:20:50.810 --> 03:20:54.691
Yogi: Yes, it's a reproduction of a very
famous painting.

03:20:54.892 --> 03:20:57.786
Shri Mataji: What’s the name?
Yogi: Vermeer. Shri Mataji: Vermeer.

03:20:57.987 --> 03:21:01.183
Yogi: Same painter as we gave to You
in the last Puja. It’s the “Coronation”.

03:21:01.384 --> 03:21:05.020
Shri Mataji: Yes, yes, yes. Yogi: Together.
Shri Mataji: Ah. That's good.

03:21:05.221 --> 03:21:08.935
Just now everything is in Shudy Camps,
so we’ll see.

03:21:09.136 --> 03:21:12.248
Beautiful. How detailed working,
I must say.

03:21:12.449 --> 03:21:14.755
You see, these days the artists are
all lazy lumps,

03:21:14.956 --> 03:21:19.710
they’ll just put a line and say it is art.
Look at this (side?).

03:21:19.911 --> 03:21:22.585
Let them have a look, beautiful.

03:21:23.719 --> 03:21:27.598
Yogi: Shri Mataji, this (on the painting)
is the ashram in Amsterdam.

03:21:27.883 --> 03:21:30.318
Shri Mataji: Beg your pardon?
Yogi: This is the ashram in Amsterdam.

03:21:30.519 --> 03:21:36.572
This is the ashram in Amsterdam…
Shri Mataji: Yes, yes. Yes. You can…

03:21:36.773 --> 03:21:42.704
Other yogi: Shri Mataji, this is a small
present from Swiss for people to France.

03:21:43.092 --> 03:21:46.496
Shri Mataji: Ah. Thank you.

03:21:49.893 --> 03:21:51.919
You brought the presents I gave you
to show them?

03:21:52.120 --> 03:21:56.262
We should have brought the presents, to
show them, that I gave you, both of you.

03:21:56.487 --> 03:21:58.633
Yogi: Oh, yes... Shri Mataji: The leaders.
You have got it? Yogi: No.

03:21:58.834 --> 03:22:01.221
Shri Mataji: No? All right.

03:22:01.882 --> 03:22:05.685
Yes, we could show them later on.

03:22:13.204 --> 03:22:18.571
Gavin, you must be tired now. You can
give it to somebody else.

03:22:24.534 --> 03:22:27.781
Yogi (joking): So hot vibrations…

03:22:32.606 --> 03:22:35.551
Shri Mataji: Could be…

03:22:37.896 --> 03:22:40.707
This is true!

03:22:54.224 --> 03:23:00.689
This is for fanning Me, sir. You have
to fan Me, that’s why.

03:23:05.742 --> 03:23:11.478
Ah, beautiful. Beautiful. Thank you.

03:23:11.733 --> 03:23:16.086
The right time, right thing. Right time,
right thing.

03:23:16.444 --> 03:23:23.812
Right time, right thing. Very spontaneous.
Yes.

03:23:25.710 --> 03:23:30.769
Beautiful. Because you had no fan,
so they brought one.

03:23:31.000 --> 03:23:34.404
(The yogi translator mixes up the word “fan”
in French so that that it sounds like:

03:23:34.612 --> 03:23:41.077
“We had no elephant for the puja and
now we have” – everybody laughs)

03:23:41.450 --> 03:23:44.323
Yogi translator: Fan.

03:23:45.198 --> 03:23:50.622
Shri Mataji: What’s he telling? Yogi: He
said, “They had no elephant for the puja…”

03:23:50.902 --> 03:23:54.220
Shri Mataji: All right, take it.

03:24:04.735 --> 03:24:09.419
Yogi: As Guido asked: “Do you feel
the cool breeze now, of our Mother?

03:24:09.650 --> 03:24:12.012
Shri Mataji: I know, when I’m perspiring,
you are feeling cool breeze,

03:24:12.213 --> 03:24:15.403
of that I’m very sure.

03:24:20.268 --> 03:24:23.498
Yes, what is that now?

03:24:24.501 --> 03:24:26.733
Yogi: A present from Belgium for the French
people.

03:24:26.934 --> 03:24:35.258
Shri Mataji: Oh, it’s beautiful!
Yogi: Easter puja in Rome.

03:24:35.459 --> 03:24:37.942
Shri Mataji: This one is?
Yogi: Easter puja in Rome.

03:24:38.143 --> 03:24:41.709
Yogi 2: Easter puja in Rome.

03:24:42.013 --> 03:24:45.347
Shri Mataji: Easter? Belgium puja?
Yogi: No, Easter puja in Roma.

03:24:45.548 --> 03:24:48.540
Shri Mataji: Oh, I see.
Yogi: In Italy.

03:24:48.978 --> 03:24:51.726
Shri Mataji: This side.

03:25:02.716 --> 03:25:05.297
Beautiful.

03:25:07.240 --> 03:25:12.912
Very beautiful. Very beautiful it is,
really.

03:25:13.231 --> 03:25:16.250
Really, very beautiful photograph.

03:25:17.300 --> 03:25:21.580
Very symmetrical, beautiful, beautiful.

03:25:21.781 --> 03:25:25.498
This last – this time when we had puja?
This, in Easter?

03:25:25.699 --> 03:25:28.857
Yogis: Yes, Shri Mataji.
Shri Mataji: Ah. Really?

03:25:43.677 --> 03:25:47.566
Beautiful, very beautiful.

03:25:48.458 --> 03:25:52.714
Yogi: Havan in Alpe Motta. The havan
in Alpe Motta.

03:25:52.915 --> 03:25:56.625
Yogi: Of the havan of this year
on Sahastrara Day, in Alpe Motta.

03:25:56.826 --> 03:26:00.247
Shri Mataji: In? Yogi: Alpe Motta.
Yogi 2: In Italy. Shri Mataji: In Italy.

03:26:00.448 --> 03:26:03.754
Yogi 2: It’s a Havana, yes, during
the Sahastrara Day seminar in Italy.

03:26:03.955 --> 03:26:06.301
Shri Mataji: Ah.

03:26:16.108 --> 03:26:19.394
Beautiful! And what is that?

03:26:23.766 --> 03:26:28.453
Beautiful it is, isn’t it? What dimensions
they have taken.

03:26:28.654 --> 03:26:34.170
All the deities are sitting here, and
blessing them.

03:26:34.849 --> 03:26:38.160
May God bless you. Beautiful.

03:26:40.101 --> 03:26:47.121
Yes. Arneau: Shri Mataji, just would like
to show You the poster we put in Geneva…

03:26:47.322 --> 03:26:53.287
… of Geneva for the exhibition.
And it was very nice.

03:26:55.680 --> 03:27:00.017
Shri Mataji: It’s beautiful! Arneau: It’s
huge! It’s bigger than any other exhibition.

03:27:00.218 --> 03:27:03.249
Shri Mataji: Ah? Arneau: It’s bigger than
any other exhibition...

03:27:03.450 --> 03:27:05.902
Shri Mataji: But they want to have
a objection to Shri Ganesh!

03:27:06.103 --> 03:27:09.143
Arneau: I mean, no Shri Mataji, absolutely
not. On the contrary,

03:27:09.344 --> 03:27:13.713
people at the place of the exhibition, they
congratulated us for the posters.

03:27:13.914 --> 03:27:16.649
Shri Mataji: Oh, I see. That’s good that.
Arneau: It’s quite unusual in Geneva,

03:27:16.850 --> 03:27:20.728
I must say, but there’s a lot of France,
Shri Mataji.

03:27:22.750 --> 03:27:28.659
Shri Mataji: Beautiful. It’s very nice.
Beautiful.

03:27:29.645 --> 03:27:33.870
Very remarkable. Very balanced.

03:27:34.149 --> 03:27:37.229
The yogi translator explains: The deities
in the history of spiritual evolution –

03:27:37.430 --> 03:27:40.458
exhibition by Sahaja Yoga.
Shri Mataji: Who has drawn that?

03:27:40.659 --> 03:27:44.447
Arneau: This is Pascal, and Richard and
Christian, there were three of them.

03:27:44.648 --> 03:27:47.981
Shri Mataji: Very nice. It’s beautiful.
Really.

03:27:50.604 --> 03:27:55.979
Now, I hope the list is over, and I…

03:28:08.481 --> 03:28:12.044
Yogi: What would you like to do,
Shri Mataji? Shri Mataji: I’ll go home,

03:28:12.245 --> 03:28:16.351
but the food is brought here. We’ll -
can eat it there. Yogi: We can,

03:28:16.552 --> 03:28:18.800
there is a point to eat for You and Mr C.P.
if You want, [Shri Mataji: Eh?]

03:28:19.001 --> 03:28:22.011
or we’ll go to the hotel. Shri Mataji: He
would like to have it there I know.

03:28:22.212 --> 03:28:26.399
Yogi: Yes. Shri Mataji: So we’ll go back,
let us, so the food can go with us,

03:28:26.600 --> 03:28:28.653
they can heat it and give it to us there.

03:28:28.854 --> 03:28:31.430
Yogi: Yes, good. Shri Mataji: All right.
Would be better.

03:28:31.631 --> 03:28:36.339
Shri Mataji: But I also, you know – puja
means My situation is bad.

03:28:36.540 --> 03:28:38.889
May God bless you.

03:28:53.330 --> 03:28:56.561
There’s a sweater also.

03:28:59.161 --> 03:29:02.091
The sari, sort of - lots of things.

03:29:24.269 --> 03:29:26.813
May God bless you.

03:29:27.014 --> 03:29:29.240
Don’t go in the sun now.

03:29:29.441 --> 03:29:32.750
Today it’s horrible, I mean, one should not
go in the sun.

03:29:36.647 --> 03:29:41.052
It was good, very good.

03:29:43.548 --> 03:29:46.478
(Aside to a Yogini) Christine, you’ll have
to help Me out.

03:29:47.282 --> 03:29:54.261
